intro: Ennealophus foliosus subsp. foliosus, commonly known as the leafy ennealophus, is a member of the Apiaceae family. It is characterized by its finely divided, fern-like leaves that give it a delicate appearance. The plant typically grows in moist, shaded environments such as woodlands and stream banks. Its small, white flowers are arranged in umbels, a common feature among members of its family. The subspecies is distinguished by its broader leaves compared to other subspecies within the species.
